    <h1>Stakeholder Interaction</h1>

    <h2>2.1 Primary Stakeholder</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>DESIGNER</th>
            <th>USER</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>1. What crops or livestock do you currently produce?</td>
            <td>Chillies, Cabbages, Tomatoes, and Coriander</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>2. Can you describe your farming practices, including any sustainable or organic methods you employ?</td>
            <td>Currently use inorganic methods like synthetic chemicals, such as fertilizers and pesticides to increase crop production.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>3. What are the main challenges you face in your day-to-day operations?</td>
            <td>Inflation of fertilizers, lack of agricultural technology awareness, and insufficient irrigation facilities.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>4. How do you manage factors like weather variability that can impact your yields?</td>
            <td>Soil and water management, high-yield variety seeds, and effective drainage facilities.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>5. What technologies or innovations have you implemented on your farm?</td>
            <td>Tractors and Drip Irrigation System.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>6. What markets do you sell your products to, and how do you ensure a consistent supply and quality?</td>
            <td>Sell to several markets, ensuring quality by checking materials before selling.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>7. How do you handle issues related to labour, such as finding and retaining skilled workers?</td>
            <td>Labour management is challenging due to government schemes making workers less motivated.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>8. How do you stay informed about changes in regulations, market trends, and new technologies?</td>
            <td>Through news, markets, and fellow farmers.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>9. What government policies or initiatives have impacted your farming operations?</td>
            <td>The Pradhan Mantri Kisan Samman Nidhi (PM-KISAN) scheme.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>10. What challenges do you face in managing pests and diseases?</td>
            <td>Human health risks and environmental impacts.</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

    <hr>

    <h2>2.2 Secondary Stakeholder</h2>
    <table>
        <tr>
            <th>DESIGNER</th>
            <th>USER</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>1. How long have you been in the business of selling vegetables/fruits?</td>
            <td>2-3 decades.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>2. What types of vegetables/fruits do you typically sell, and where do you source them from?</td>
            <td>Vegetables: Tomato, Potato, Coriander<br>Fruits: Watermelon, Pomegranate, Apples</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>3. What factors influence your pricing decisions?</td>
            <td>Based on market prices, news, and profit margins.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>4. What improvements would benefit your business?</td>
            <td>Proper stalls, non-plastic bags, and better transportation of goods.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>5. Have you implemented any sustainability practices in your business?</td>
            <td>Reducing water usage, minimizing waste, and using biodegradable packaging.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>6. How do weather conditions or market trends impact your business?</td>
            <td>Extreme weather often leads to produce spoilage.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>7. How do you prefer to receive updates about market trends?</td>
            <td>Through news and fellow vendors.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>8. How do you collaborate with other stakeholders like farmers or wholesalers?</td>
            <td>Purchase goods from farmers and sell them to consumers for profit.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td>9. How do you manage waste or spoilage of produce?</td>
            <td>Wastes are typically discarded as they are hard to manage.</td>
        </tr>
    </table>

